(Matsumura, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
transmits tomato big bud, tobacco yellow dwarf, lucerne witches’ broom, legume little leaf, mosaic I, potato purple top wilt, and witches’ broom of groundnuts. 
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A337FF9FACA1E4E72F71FA13" authority="Distant, 1918" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1918" box="[673,1071,1456,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Orosius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicinctus">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A337FF9FACA1E4E728D9FA13" box="[673,903,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Orosius albicinctus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="853B70E7A337FF9FAD8FE4E72F71FA13" author="Distant W. L." box="[911,1071,1456,1482]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" refId="ref85887" refString="Distant W. L. 1918. Rhynchota. Homoptera: Appendix. Heteroptera: Addenda. In: Shipley A. E. &amp; Marshall G. A. K. (eds) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Volume 7. Taylor and Francis, London." type="book" year="1918">Distant, 1918</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
transmits sesame phyllody. 
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A337FF9FAEBDE4842934FA34" authority="(Distant, 1908)" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[189,618,1491,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phycitis">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A337FF9FAEBDE4842AF3FA34" box="[189,429,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Hishimonus phycitis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="853B70E7A337FF9FAFBFE484293CFA34" author="Distant W. L." box="[447,610,1491,1517]" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" refId="ref85845" refString="Distant W. L. 1908. Rhynchota - Homoptera. In: Bingham C. T. (ed.) The Fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma. Volume 4. Taylor and Francis, London." type="book" year="1908">Distant, 1908</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
vectors eggplant little leaf. 
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A337FF9FADBBE4842BA6F9C8" authority="Ishihara, 1965" authorityName="Ishihara" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sellatiformis">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A337FF9FADBBE4842E56FA34" box="[955,1288,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Hishimonoides sellatiformis</emphasis>
Ishihara, 1965
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="26AA7695A337FF9FAF36E4A1298CF9C8" authority="(Uhler, 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Uhler" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[310,722,1526,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="121" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sellatus">
<emphasis id="D3DED104A337FF9FAF36E4A12979F9C9" box="[310,551,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="121" pageNumber="122">Hishimonus sellatus</emphasis>
(Uhler, 1896)
</taxonomicName>
are vectors of mulberry dwarf and the latter leafhopper is also a vector of Rhus yellows, jujube witches’ broom, and 
